parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the motorcycle to suddenly lose power, slip out of gear, or lock up, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission slips out of gear
jumps out of gear
or locks up
causing the motorcycle to lose power or speed suddenly. The transmission may also make loud clunking or grinding noises
or produce a false neutral between gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to quit while in traffic, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine dies while driving or at a stop
the vehicle will not restart
the vehicle must be towed to a residence or dealership.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank sending unit can cause fuel leakage and fumes, posing a fire hazard and potentially causing damage to the vehicle or surrounding property.
symptoms: Fuel leakage
fuel fumes
puddles of gas on the garage floor
saturated padding around the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of control and increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Surging or pulsing sensation when applying the brakes
especially at low speeds (under 20mph)
uneven brake pedal feel
vibrations when braking
reduced braking performance
and increased risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Repeated transmission failures can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the failure occurs at high speeds.
symptoms: Loss of power
transmission slipping
unusual noises
difficulty shifting gears
and complete transmission failure.
